This paper deals with the design and analysis of codes for distributed storage systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), distributed computing (cs.DC), and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the matrix representation of fractional repetition codes, which is a common technique in signal processing and communications (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the rate of codes, which is a fundamental concept in networking and information theory (cs.NI).
